author: The Capital-Journal
title: C-J's high school football rankings
text:
C-J's high school football rankings Posted: October 18, 2015 - 3:44pm 
Woods sets Lions’ career rushing record in win over Olathe Northwest 
2. Wichita Northwest (2) 7-0 
Injured Grizzly QB Folsom come off bench to lead rally past Dodge City 
3. Mill Valley (3) 6-1 
Jaguars recover from early deficit, win huge showdown with No. 4 St. James 
4. Topeka High (4) 7-0 
Trojans get trio of 100-yard rushers; defense comes up big in win over Manhattan 
5. SM East (5) 6-1 
East has no troubles rolling past KC Harmon 69-0 
6. Derby (6) 6-1 
Panthers stymie Campus passing game in rout 
7. Miege (7) 6-1 
Stags’ offensive stars efficient in romp past Spring Hill 
8. Junction City (8) 7-0 
No hangover after Manhattan win for Jays, who post fourth shutout 
9. Olathe North (9) 7-0 
North rolls into huge clash with No. 1 Lawrence 
10. Garden City (NR) 7-0 
Buffaloes corral Hutchinson in 14-2 win 
CLASS 6A 
2. Wichita Northwest (2) 7-0 
3. Topeka High (3) 7-0 
4. SM East (4) 5-1 
5. Derby (5) 5-1 
Others — Blue Valley 5-2, BV North 6-1, Free State 4-3, Garden City 7-0, Hutchinson 5-2, Junction City 7-0, Manhattan 4-3, Olathe North 7-0, Olathe Northwest 5-2, SM West 6-1, Washburn Rural 5-2. 
Notes — Down 21-14 to Dodge City after a Red Demon pick-six, Wichita Northwest was in danger of seeing its undefeated season come to an end. But senior quarterback Kevin Folsom, who suffered a partially-torn left medial-collateral knee ligament last week against Wichita South, came off the bench to rally the Grizzlies to a 52-33 victory, throwing for 267 yards and four touchdowns. 
CLASS 5A 
1. Mill Valley (1) 6-1 
2. Pittsburg (2) 7-0 
4. Bonner Springs (5) 7-0 
5. St. James Academy (4) 6-1 
Others — Aquinas 5-2, Goddard 4-3, Great Bend 5-2, Kapaun 5-2, Maize South 6-1, Salina South 4-3, Wichita Heights 5-2. 
Notes — Mill Valley raced out to a quick 10-0 lead in its showdown with No. 4 St. James Academy, but saw the Thunder storm back for a 14-10 lead. From there, however, it was all Jaguars as Mill Valley scored the final 35 points for a 45-14 win behind 269 yards passing from Logan Koch. 
CLASS 4A DIVISION I
